# Request
float64 duration_sec    # ignored — kept for caller-API compat. The motion
                        # profile fixed in the calibrate_imu_yaw_node now
                        # dictates how long sample collection takes.
string job_id           # caller-issued identifier, echoed in the published
                        # CalibrateImuYawStatus messages so a subscriber can
                        # ignore stale `transient_local` cached statuses from
                        # a previous run.
---
# Response
# This service ONLY indicates whether the calibration was accepted to start.
# The full result (yaw / pitch / roll / sample counts / etc.) is published on
# the `~/calibrate_status` topic when the run finishes — see
# mowgli_interfaces/msg/CalibrateImuYawStatus.
#
# Why split? When this service's response carried 12 mixed-type fields, the
# foxglove_bridge ↔ rmw_cyclonedds GenericClient dispatch path failed to
# resolve the response typesupport, breaking the GUI's calibrate button (#19).
# A single-bool response goes through the same dispatch happily — that's the
# pattern used elsewhere in this package (see SetDockingPoint).
bool success
